class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="cravins-candy-emporium" class="entry-website-title">Cravin&#039;s Candy Emporium</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-cravins-candy-emporium-2024073-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-cravins-candy-emporium-2024073-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-cravins-candy-emporium-2024073-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Cravin&#039;s Candy Emporium"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://cravinscandy.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://cravinscandy.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Boise, Idaho, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Cravin's Candy Emporium is a neighborhood candy store with four locations around the U.S. They specialize in retro candy, glass bottle sodas, gelatos, and chocolates and aim to bring that nostalgic candy experience to future generations. The site highlights the children-focused niche through bright candy colors.</p><p>High-quality images full of laughing children and colorful candy draw attention to the fun, family-friendly vibe. The site goes a step further by highlighting their scavenger hunt event for birthday parties. Visitors can also shop for candy and gift cards online.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site has an esthetic design with high-quality images and clear contact details, location, and store hours are provided. Customer reviews are included on the contact page and the site features a floating menu to aid in navigation.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>According to accessScan, the site is not compliant with assistive technologies and WAVE reports a number of empty headings and contrast errors. The online shop lacks product descriptions or ingredients.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-cravins-candy-emporium-2024073-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-cravins-candy-emporium-2024073-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop site offers visitors both a sticky top menu and a footer menu in different colors. The social media links are in the footer menu but may be overlooked as they're in the same colors and font as the rest of the footer menu.</p><p>The desktop site scores exceptionally well on Google's PageSpeed Insights test, with 100/100 for best practices, 90/100 for accessibility, and 94/100 for performance. However, our real-world tests did show some lags in loading times for the online shop.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-cravins-candy-emporium-2024073-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-cravins-candy-emporium-2024073-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>With the vertical layout of the mobile site, it seems to be more text-heavy than the desktop version but is well-optimized to fit smaller screens. The hamburger menu travels with the reader as they scroll — a stand-out feature that ensures easy navigation. Real-world tests also showed slow loading times in the mobile online shop,  and PageSpeed Insights confirms these findings with a performance score of 43/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="sugar-sin" class="entry-website-title">SugarSin</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sugar-sin-20240621-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sugar-sin-20240621-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sugar-sin-20240621-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website SugarSin"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://sugarsin.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://sugarsin.co.uk/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Covent Garden, England, U.K.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>SugarSin is a gourmet confectionery store specializing in cocktail-inspired gummies, chocolates, and vegan, gluten-free, and dairy-free candies. The site features bright, high-quality images and moving graphics to engage the visitor. There is an online shopping feature, a wishlist feature, and a login option for visitors to create their own accounts.</p><p>Visitors to the site can view a range of different candies and styles (including gifts and subscriptions) for purchase, while the business's story, customer care options, and social media links are available in the footer.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The menu options are clearly defined, with online shopping categories available in the floating top menu and business information available in the footer. The addition of customer reviews and awards won builds customer trust.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is only semi-compliant with assistive technologies and WAVE reports a number of empty links, missing alternative text, and contrast errors. The site lacks a GPS location option to find the physical store, and a link to the business information in the footer would aid navigation.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sugar-sin-20240621-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sugar-sin-20240621-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop site stands out with bright colors that reflect the colorful, sweet nature of the candies on sale. The shopping cart, wishlist, and login links are all helpfully available in the floating top menu. CTAs are prominent in colors opposite to the background they appear on, enhancing the fun design. However, despite strong real-world experiences, the desktop site scores an average of 62/100 for performance on PageSpeed Insights.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sugar-sin-20240621-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sugar-sin-20240621-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site is well-optimized, maintaining engaging visuals but offering a brighter color palette than on the desktop. The CTAs also stand out more with the brighter color palette. Unlike the desktop site, the mobile site only highlights the wishlist in the top menu, with the shopping cart and search function available in the hamburger menu.</p><p>The login function, however, appears to be missing from the mobile site, which seems more compact than the desktop version. Despite strong real-world tests, PageSpeed Insights reports slow loading times, leading to a performance score of 42/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
