https://lolly-kingdom.com.au/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Ulladulla, New South Wales, Australia</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Lolly Kingdom is an online mix-and-match candy store that has expanded to include physical stores across Australia. The site features a somewhat overwhelming selection of menu items and different candy options to choose from, and the design highlights a great cookie-cutter pattern, reminiscent of old-school paper bags of candy, perfect for their brand message. A candy-focused blog is a great addition to the site.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site's branding and design are on-point, complementing the brand message of the business. In contrast to the busy menu, the footer is clean and offers visitors information on operating hours, social media links, and contact details.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is not compliant with assistive technologies and WAVE reports a large number of broken ARIA references, which impact the use of assistive technologies, and contrast errors. The site's menu is overwhelming, especially for the children that are the target market, and the "Contact Us" and "About Us" pages get lost among all the candy options.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-lolly-kingdom-20240621-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
