<span>Plumstead, Western Cape, South Africa</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Grifits is a candy store based in South Africa that offers customers a range of South African and international candies. The business aims for a nostalgic aesthetic, highlighted on its site through a pink color palette and a handwritten-styled typeface. The site features various options, from wholesale candy to gift boxes and treats for school lunches.</p><p>The store location, contact details, and operating hours are prominently displayed at the bottom of the home page, along with social media links. The site offers only three pages and the lack of an online shopping feature is noticeable. Instead, the company uses WhatsApp and email for orders.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE reports just one empty heading and three contrast errors. The site is simple, leading to an easy user experience, with the store location, contact details, and operating hours clearly visible on the site.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is semi-compliant with assistive technologies and lacks an online shopping feature. The gallery page features a simple block with a range of images inside it, as well as a long text block that shows poor legibility.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-grifits-candy-20240621-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
